### 3.3.1 Advanced DN  

#### Exercise 23 DN

Divide mpg dataframe into 2 halves and plot 2 separate geom_point graphs  with displ on x-axis and hwy on y-axis  respectively.
**Note**:"spliting the mpg dataframe requires floor(), set.seed(), sample(), seq(). You many want to get help on this functions first". Also, note we are getting a random sample for each of the 2 halves.

<div class="tutorial-exercise" data-label="D23" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
half_size <- floor(0.5*  )
set.seed(123123)
mpg_half <- sample(seq(   ), size= half_size)

mpg_1 <- mpg[mpg_half, ]
mpg_2 <- mpg[-mpg_half, ]

ggplot(data= mpg_1) +
  geom_point(  )
ggplot(data=mpg_2) +
  geom_point(  )
```

<script type="application/json" data-ui-opts="1">{"engine":"r","has_checker":true,"caption":"<span data-i18n=\"text.enginecap\" data-i18n-opts=\"{&quot;engine&quot;:&quot;R&quot;}\">R Code<\/span>"}</script></div>

<div class="tutorial-exercise-support" data-label="D23-solution" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
half_size <- floor(0.5*nrow(mpg))
set.seed(123123)
mpg_half <- sample(seq(nrow(mpg)),size= half_size)

mpg_1 <- mpg[mpg_half, ]
mpg_2 <- mpg[-mpg_half, ]

ggplot(data= mpg_1) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x= displ, y = hwy))
ggplot(data=mpg_2) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x= displ, y = hwy))
```

</div>

## Section 3.5.1 SD

### 3.5.1 Easy SD


Let's try making facets for our mpg data and displ as x and hwy as y. Use facet_wrap() on any one categorical variable & facet_grid() on any two categorical variables. Can you see the difference?
<div class="tutorial-exercise" data-label="Facet" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
ggplot(data=)+geom_point()+
  
ggplot(data=)+geom_point()+  
```

<script type="application/json" data-ui-opts="1">{"engine":"r","has_checker":false,"caption":"<span data-i18n=\"text.enginecap\" data-i18n-opts=\"{&quot;engine&quot;:&quot;R&quot;}\">R Code<\/span>"}</script></div>

<div class="tutorial-exercise-support" data-label="Facet-hint-1" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
"the first argument of facet_wrap() is a tilda followed by the categorical variable "
"remember a tilda looks like this: ~"
```

</div>
<div class="tutorial-exercise-support" data-label="Facet-hint-2" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
"the argument of facet_grid() has two variables separated by a tilda "
```

</div>

<div class="tutorial-exercise-support" data-label="Facet-solution" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)
  
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_grid(drv ~ cyl)
```

</div>

```text
flights %>%
```

```text
  group_by(year, month, day) %>%
```

```text
  ggplot(aes(first_dep,last_arr)) +
  geom_smooth()
```

### 5.6.7 Challenging KA

What time of day should you fly if you want to avoid delays as much as possible?
 
 <div class="tutorial-exercise" data-label="two-plus-fivec" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0"><script type="application/json" data-ui-opts="1">{"engine":"r","has_checker":true,"caption":"<span data-i18n=\"text.enginecap\" data-i18n-opts=\"{&quot;engine&quot;:&quot;R&quot;}\">R Code<\/span>"}</script></div>
<div class="tutorial-exercise-support" data-label="two-plus-fivec-solution" data-completion="1" data-diagnostics="1" data-startover="1" data-lines="0">

```text
flights %>%
  group_by(hour) %>%
  summarise(arr_delay = mean(arr_delay, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  arrange(arr_delay)
```
